inaxModemTable.name: inaxModemTable
inaxModemTable.description: This table contains information about all INAX units in all racks.

mdmRack.name: mdmRack
mdmRack.description: The index of the rack where the unit is installed.

mdmModem.name: mdmModem
mdmModem.description: This entry displays the slot number where the corresponding unit is installed in the rack.

mdmPosition.name: mdmPosition
mdmPosition.description: This entry displays the location of the corresponding unit: 'local' or 'remote'. The unit which is plugged into a managed rack is 'local', the counterpart is 'remote'.

mdmModemName.name: mdmModemName
mdmModemName.description: The verbal name of this unit.

mdmModemProperty.name: mdmModemProperty
mdmModemProperty.description: The speed class of the unit: 'e1' or 't1'.

mdmActiveLink.name: mdmActiveLink
mdmActiveLink.description: This entry displays the line port that is receiving data.

mdmRemoteAccessMode.name: mdmRemoteAccessMode
mdmRemoteAccessMode.description: This entry defines the time slot assigned for remote management. Remote management is realized via port 5 always. For T1 units 24 time slots are available only. The remote unit's configuration changes simultaneously.

inaxIFPortTable.name: inaxIFPortTable
inaxIFPortTable.description: This table contains information about all I/F ports of the INAX units in all racks.

iportRack.name: iportRack
iportRack.description: The index of the rack where the unit is installed.

iportModem.name: iportModem
iportModem.description: The index of the INAX unit the port belongs to.

iportPosition.name: iportPosition
iportPosition.description: This entry displays the location of the corresponding port: 'local' or 'remote'. The port which is plugged into a managed rack is 'local', the counterpart is 'remote'.

iportDataEmulationMode.name: iportDataEmulationMode
iportDataEmulationMode.description: Interface mode of the port: 'dte', 'dce', 'te', or 'nt'.

iportDataRate.name: iportDataRate
iportDataRate.description: The data rate at the interface port in bits per seconds.

iportTimeslotSize.name: iportTimeslotSize
iportTimeslotSize.description: This entry determines the size of the time slots: 'nx64k' or 'nx56k'. 'nx56k' is valid for T1 units only. The remote unit's configuration changes simultaneously.

inaxLinePortTable.name: inaxLinePortTable
inaxLinePortTable.description: This table contains information about all line ports of the INAX units in all racks.

lportRack.name: lportRack
lportRack.description: The index of the rack where the unit is installed.

lportModem.name: lportModem
lportModem.description: The index of the INAX unit the port belongs to.

lportPosition.name: lportPosition
lportPosition.description: This entry displays the location of the corresponding port: 'local' or 'remote'. The port which is plugged into a managed rack is 'local', the counterpart is 'remote'.

lportDataEmulationMode.name: lportDataEmulationMode
lportDataEmulationMode.description: Interface mode of the port: 'te' or 'nt'.

lportClockSource.name: lportClockSource
lportClockSource.description: The clock source: 'internal' or 'remote'. Port 4 can only be set to 'internal'.

lportDataRate.name: lportDataRate
lportDataRate.description: The data rate at the line port in bits per seconds.

lportCRC4Generation.name: lportCRC4Generation
lportCRC4Generation.description: This entry enables or disables the generation of a CRC4 check sum. The remote unit's configuration changes simultaneously. Valid for E1 units only.

lportFramingMode.name: lportFramingMode
lportFramingMode.description: The T1 framing mode: 'd4' or 'esf'. The remote unit's configuration changes simultaneously. Valid for T1 units only.

lportCodingMode.name: lportCodingMode
lportCodingMode.description: The T1 coding mode at port 4: 'ami' or 'b8zs'. The remote unit's configuration changes simultaneously. Valid for T1 units only.

lportLineBuiltOut.name: lportLineBuiltOut
lportLineBuiltOut.description: The G.703 transmission mode of the unit.

lportPortMode.name: lportPortMode
lportPortMode.description: The operation mode at port 4: 'interface-mode', 'backup-mode', or 'link-mode'.

lportCRC6Test.name: lportCRC6Test
lportCRC6Test.description: This entry enables the execution of a CRC6 test. Write requests with values other than 'start' or 'stop' will be rejected. Valid for T1 units only.

lportCRC6Status.name: lportCRC6Status
lportCRC6Status.description: This entry indicates the status of the CRC6 test. Valid for T1 units only.

lportCRC6Error.name: lportCRC6Error
lportCRC6Error.description: This entry indicates the number of errors detected during the last 60 seconds.

inaxTimeslotTable.name: inaxTimeslotTable
inaxTimeslotTable.description: This table contains information about all line ports of the INAX units in all racks.

tsRack.name: tsRack
tsRack.description: The index of the rack where the unit is installed.

tsModem.name: tsModem
tsModem.description: The index of the INAX unit the port belongs to.

tsPosition.name: tsPosition
tsPosition.description: This entry displays the location of the corresponding port: 'local' or 'remote'. The port which is plugged into a managed rack is 'local', the counterpart is 'remote'.

tsTimeslot1.name: tsTimeslot1
tsTimeslot1.description: This entry defines the port number used for the transmission of time slot 1. 'port-4' is available only if IportPortmode is set to 'interface-mode'. If the time slot is assigned for remote management (see mdmRemoteAccessMode).
